main event: On April 4, 1965, two bright objects were observed moving at high speeds in Clearwater.
interesting points: The objects were seen appearing as stars but were traveling at a high rate of speed,The observation lasted for about 5 minutes,The objects were moving straight at an extremely high altitude of 31,000 feet,The report concludes the objects were likely satellites reflecting sunlight,The sighting occurred while looking north at 135 degrees.
witness description: observer believed to be reliable and his wife also observed the objects
